{"TopicId":161724,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Radial heatshield tiles?","CreatedByName":"telomce","CreatedById":177795,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-07T09:06:07Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"telomce","CreatedById":177795,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-07T09:06:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSometimes on really harsh reentries, on Eve especially, long and narrow stuff flips and overheats. So why not add a radial heatshield to fit of surfaces with barely any protection?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Noud","CreatedById":176567,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-07T09:38:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYES!! we need this\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nprobably a mod already.. but if not someone will make one\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"steuben","CreatedById":77368,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-07T11:54:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr maybe\u00A0something like an\u00A0aeroshell with an ablator rating. Some prototype discussions are \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/161322-ablative-fairing\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ehere\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy mental video of the fairing blowing off in packet-of-crisps mode with just a bit of the atmospheric fire effects still in place... cool.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheKorbinjer","CreatedById":172204,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-07T14:51:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 Would you like to buy radial heat shields for $0.99?\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u0026gt; YES\u00A0\u0026lt;\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003E NO\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003EHad to.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003EI think it\u0027d be cool to see radial shields added. It\u0027d go nice with my shuttles. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"qzgy","CreatedById":160994,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-07T15:27:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs it really necessary? Couldn\u0027t you stick a couple of radiators onto it to help dissipate heat.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, a well designed reentry should help mitigate heat problems.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheKorbinjer","CreatedById":172204,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-07T16:16:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTrue, but it would add some realism. NASA doesn\u0027t add ugly thin pieces of metal outside of their spacecraft on reentry.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot to mention, IRL those would just evaporate on reentry\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ZooNamedGames","CreatedById":103726,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-07T19:28:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223083777\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161724\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496852175\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022172204\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022TheKorbinger\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, TheKorbinger said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTrue, but it would add some realism. NASA doesn\u0027t add ugly thin pieces of metal outside of their spacecraft on reentry.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot to mention, IRL those would just evaporate on reentry\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIndeed. In real life they\u0027d struggle to dissipate heat fast enough (that is if they don\u0027t evaporate). Personally I think this would help if we could angle snap on a flat bottom to the curved mk2/mk3 bottoms and from there you could attach thermal \u0022plates\u0022 to simulate large sections of the thermal panels for spaceplanes. Noting they don\u0027t ablate, they just have a high melting point.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DrLicor","CreatedById":165712,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-07T19:37:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/141068-pak/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022141068\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/141068-pak/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Pak\u003C/a\u003E has made some real nice MK3 shuttle parts with include radial/bottom parts of heatshield.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nThese are only for the MK3 parts, however, you could give it a try by down- or up-scaling it for the other parts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/119951-13-cormorant-aeronology/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NSEP","CreatedById":165635,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-10T21:28:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr/and ablative fairings?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ZooNamedGames","CreatedById":103726,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-10T23:30:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223084015\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161724\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496864239\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165712\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DrLicor\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 6/7/2017 at 3:37 PM, DrLicor said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/141068-pak/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022141068\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/141068-pak/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Pak\u003C/a\u003E has made some real nice MK3 shuttle parts with include radial/bottom parts of heatshield.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nThese are only for the MK3 parts, however, you could give it a try by down- or up-scaling it for the other parts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/119951-13-cormorant-aeronology/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever we\u0027re interested in seeing this become stock.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223087303\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161724\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221497130125\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165635\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022NSEP\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, NSEP said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr/and ablative fairings?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPossibly. Personally they have never sat well with me as far as concept but I\u0027d use it if was available.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Noud","CreatedById":176567,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-13T09:22:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwell wouldn\u0027t it be more realistic that every part has some kind of ablative values?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyou can sometimes better use a engine as heat shield that an actual heat shield... as a few passes trough the atmosphere can completely wear down your heat shield... you don\u0027t have that problem with engines\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0always thought it\u00A0was bit strange.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}